The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Meeting on Nandigram

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Calcutta, April 19: The government has lined up an all-party meeting in Nandigram on Sunday to restore normality there.

 We shall join if some issues, including the March 14 firing and the rehabilitation of those who fled their homes after that, are on the agenda, East Midnapore Trinamul Congress president and MLA Sisir Adhikari said. SP Anil Srinivas had spoken to him about the meeting, he added.

 Leader of the Opposition and Trinamul MLA Partha Chatterjee said Mamata Banerjee would take a decision on participating in the meet.




